{"title":"How to Remove White Space Generated by inline-block?","date":"2020-02-22T10:32:33.000Z","date_formatted":{"ll":"Feb 22, 2020","L":"02/22/2020","MM-DD":"02-22"},"thumbnail":"https://img.cdn.n3ko.co/lsky/2020/02/22/c708b703db2a5.png?x-oss-process=image/auto-orient,1/quality,q_70/sharpen,200/format,webp","link":"2020/02/22/How-to-Remove-White-Space-generated-by-Inside-Block","comments":true,"tags":["css"],"categories":["Programming"],"updated":"2020-03-05T06:49:33.017Z","content":"<blockquote>\n<p>Partial reference from: <a href=\"http://css-tricks.com/fighting-the-space-between-inline-block-elements/\" target=\"_blank\">http://css-tricks.com/fighting-the-space-between-inline-block-elements/</a> </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>There is a particular term: <strong>White Space Collapse</strong> to describe this annoying “feature”. </p>\n<p>The most elegant way of solving it is by setting <code>white-space-collapse:discard</code>.</p>\n<p>e.g.,</p>\n<figure class=\"highlight css\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"selector-tag\">ul</span>&#123;</span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"attribute\">white-space-collapse</span>:discard;</span><br><span class=\"line\">&#125;</span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"selector-tag\">li</span>&#123;</span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"attribute\">display</span>:inline-block;</span><br><span class=\"line\">&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<p>Yet, this attribute is not supported by many mainstream browsers. </p>\n<p>Other solutions:</p>\n<ol><li><p>Set font-size to 0. The shortcoming of this method is that it requires rewriting font-size of every sub-elements. Plus, some browsers like Safari do not allow font-size to be 0. So this may not be elegant.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Several tags, including <code>li</code>, tolerates unclosed tags. </p>\n<figure class=\"highlight html\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">ul</span> <span class=\"attr\">style</span>=<span class=\"string\">\"display:inline-block\"</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span>Happy</span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span>Goodbye</span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">ul</span>&gt;</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<p>This is barely practical under certain circumstances, let alone its violation of HTML coding conventions.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Delete spaces or write tags the other way.</p>\n<p>Deleting white spaces works, though it to some extent reduces code readability.</p>\n<figure class=\"highlight html\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">ul</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span>homepage<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span>register<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span>login<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span>about<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span>other<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"comment\">&lt;!--imagine the mess when there are more li tags and content in li--&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">ul</span>&gt;</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<p>Or, you can write code like below:</p>\n<figure class=\"highlight html\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br><span class=\"line\">7</span><br><span class=\"line\">8</span><br><span class=\"line\">9</span><br><span class=\"line\">10</span><br><span class=\"line\">11</span><br><span class=\"line\">12</span><br><span class=\"line\">13</span><br><span class=\"line\">14</span><br><span class=\"line\">15</span><br><span class=\"line\">16</span><br><span class=\"line\">17</span><br><span class=\"line\">18</span><br><span class=\"line\">19</span><br><span class=\"line\">20</span><br><span class=\"line\">21</span><br><span class=\"line\">22</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">ul</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">  <span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">   a<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">   b<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">   c<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">ul</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\">&lt;!--or--&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">ul</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">  <span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span>a<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span></span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">  &gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span>b<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span></span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">  &gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span>c<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">ul</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\">&lt;!-- or --&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">ul</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">  <span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span>a<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span><span class=\"comment\">&lt;!--</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\">  --&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span>b<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span><span class=\"comment\">&lt;!--</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\">  --&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span>c<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">li</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">ul</span>&gt;</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n</li>\n<li><p>Set a negative margin. It works, but is not recommended as well.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Not really a solution: Use <code>float</code> or <code>flexbox</code> instead.</p>\n</li>\n</ol><p>Lazy as I am, if the white space is really bothering, I’ll just giving up using <code>inline-block</code>.  After all, what’s the meaning of sticking to it?</p>\n","prev":{"title":"Basic YAML Syntax","link":"2020/02/24/Basic-YAML-Syntax"},"next":{"title":"Why ArrayList supports variable-length?","link":"2020/02/21/Why-ArrayList-supports-variable-length"},"plink":"https://git.michaelsblog.top/2020/02/22/How-to-Remove-White-Space-generated-by-Inside-Block/"}